  "root_text": {
    "an5.42:0.1": "Aṅguttara Nikāya 5.42 ",
    "an5.42:0.2": "5. Muṇḍarājavagga ",
    "an5.42:0.3": "Sappurisasutta ",
    "an5.42:1.1": "“Sappuriso, bhikkhave, kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:1.2": "mātāpitūnaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:1.3": "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:1.4": "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:1.5": "mittāmaccānaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:1.6": "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti. ",
    "an5.42:2.1": "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, mahāmegho sabbasassāni sampādento bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.2": "evamevaṁ kho, bhikkhave, sappuriso kule jāyamāno bahuno janassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.3": "mātāpitūnaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.4": "puttadārassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.5": "dāsakammakaraporisassa atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.6": "mittāmaccānaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hoti; ",
    "an5.42:2.7": "samaṇabrāhmaṇānaṁ atthāya hitāya sukhāya hotīti. ",
    "an5.42:3.1": "Hito bahunnaṁ paṭipajja bhoge, ",
    "an5.42:3.2": "Taṁ devatā rakkhati dhammaguttaṁ; ",
    "an5.42:3.3": "Bahussutaṁ sīlavatūpapannaṁ, ",
    "an5.42:3.4": "Dhamme ṭhitaṁ na vijahati kitti. ",
    "an5.42:4.1": "Dhammaṭṭhaṁ sīlasampannaṁ, ",
    "an5.42:4.2": "saccavādiṁ hirīmanaṁ; ",
    "an5.42:4.3": "Nekkhaṁ jambonadasseva, ",
    "an5.42:4.4": "ko taṁ ninditumarahati; ",
    "an5.42:4.5": "Devāpi naṁ pasaṁsanti, ",
    "an5.42:4.6": "brahmunāpi pasaṁsito”ti. ",
    "an5.42:4.7": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "an5.42:0.1": "Numbered Discourses 5.42 ",
    "an5.42:0.2": "5. With King Muṇḍa ",
    "an5.42:0.3": "A True Person ",
    "an5.42:1.1": "“Mendicants, a true person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. ",
    "an5.42:1.2": "For the benefit, welfare, and happiness of mother and father; ",
    "an5.42:1.3": "children and partners; ",
    "an5.42:1.4": "bondservants, workers, and staff; ",
    "an5.42:1.5": "friends and colleagues; ",
    "an5.42:1.6": "and ascetics and brahmins. ",
    "an5.42:2.1": "It’s like a great rain cloud, which nourishes all the crops for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. ",
    "an5.42:2.2": "In the same way, a true person is born in a family for the benefit, welfare, and happiness of the people. … ",
    "an5.42:2.3": "",
    "an5.42:2.4": "",
    "an5.42:2.5": "",
    "an5.42:2.6": "",
    "an5.42:2.7": "",
    "an5.42:3.1": "The gods protect one who is guarded by principle, ",
    "an5.42:3.2": "who uses their wealth for the welfare of the many. ",
    "an5.42:3.3": "One who is learned, <j>with precepts and observances intact, ",
    "an5.42:3.4": "and steady in principle, doesn’t lose their reputation. ",
    "an5.42:4.1": "Firm in principle, accomplished in ethical conduct, ",
    "an5.42:4.2": "truthful, conscientious; ",
    "an5.42:4.3": "like a pendant of Black Plum River gold, ",
    "an5.42:4.4": "who is worthy to criticize them? ",
    "an5.42:4.5": "Even the gods praise them, ",
    "an5.42:4.6": "and by the Divinity, too, they’re praised.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "an5.42:1.2": "mātāpitūnaṁ → mātāpitunnaṁ (bj, pts1ed) ",
    "an5.42:3.4": "vijahati → vijahāti (bj, sya-all, km, pts1ed) "
  },
